## Scope

This document covers **Stabilize mode only**: the pilot's roll/pitch sticks command an attitude (tilt vector), the yaw stick commands a yaw rate, and throttle is direct. The cascade is:

```
   sticks → attitude setpoint → OUTER LOOP (attitude) → INNER LOOP (rate) → torque → allocator → motors
```

Both loops run **closed**. The outer loop closes around the attitude estimate from EKF2; the inner loop closes around the gyro. Acro mode and the manual stick-passthrough are intentionally excluded.

