## 3. Inner loop — rate control

### 3.1 Block diagram with feedback paths

```
                                              ┌───────────────────────────────────┐
                                              │       INNER LOOP — RATE (PID)     │
                                              │                                    │
   ω_sp ──────────────────────►( Σ_e )───► err ──►[ P (per-axis) ]───►( Σ )──── × K ──► τ
                                  ▲                                    ▲ ▲ ▲
                              (−) │                                    │ │ │
                                  │                                    │ │ │
                                  │                            [ ∫I·err·dt ]  (integrator with i_factor;
                                  │                                  │ │ │     anti-windup gate dormant)
                                  │                                    │ │
                                  │                            [ FF · ω_sp ]   (default 0)
                                  │                                      │
                                  │                                      │
                                  │                                [ −D · α ]
                                  │                                      ▲
                                  │                                      │
                                  │                            ┌─────────┴────────────┐
                                  │                            │ angular accel α      │
                                  │                            │ vehicle_angular_     │
                                  │                            │  velocity            │
                                  │                            │  .xyz_derivative     │
                                  │                            └──────────────────────┘
                                  │
                                  │   RATE FEEDBACK PATH (primary)
                                  │   ━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━━
                                  │
                                  └────── ω (from gyro: vehicle_angular_velocity.xyz) ◄──── [ PLANT ]
                                                                                            (allocator
                                                                                            + motors
                                                                                            + airframe
                                                                                            + IMU)
   Notes:
   • err = ω_sp − ω is a straightforward 3-vector subtraction at the summing junction.

   • The D term uses gyro-derived angular acceleration α (= xyz_derivative), NOT
     the time-derivative of the rate error. No additional filter is applied
     inside the controller — α is already filtered upstream by VehicleAngularVelocity.

   • The integrator is updated only when !landed (rate_control.cpp:81-83).
     The "i_factor" scales I-gain down for large rate errors:
        i_factor = max(0, 1 − (err / 400°)²)

   • K is the master gain (MC_*RATE_K, default 1.0) that scales P, I, D — applied
     inside the controller via the gain setter at MulticopterRateControl.cpp:83-86.
```

### 3.2 Equation (per axis i ∈ {x, y, z})

```
    err[i] = ω_sp[i] − ω_meas[i]                                ← rate error (rad/s)
    τ[i]   = K[i] · ( P[i]·err[i]
                    + ∫_i                                       ← integrator state
                    − D[i]·α[i]                                 ← derivative on measured accel
                    + FF[i]·ω_sp[i] )                           ← feed-forward (default 0)
    ∫_i   ← clip( ∫_i + i_factor[i]·I[i]·err[i]·dt, ±lim_int[i] )    if !landed
```

### 3.3 Per-channel breakdown

| | **Roll (x)** | **Pitch (y)** | **Yaw (z)** |
|---|---|---|---|
| Setpoint source | `vehicle_rates_setpoint.roll` (from outer loop) | `.pitch` | `.yaw` |
| Rate feedback | `vehicle_angular_velocity.xyz[0]` | `.xyz[1]` | `.xyz[2]` |
| Accel feedback (for D) | `vehicle_angular_velocity.xyz_derivative[0]` | `.xyz_derivative[1]` | `.xyz_derivative[2]` |
| **P** | `MC_ROLLRATE_P` = 0.15 | `MC_PITCHRATE_P` = 0.15 | `MC_YAWRATE_P` = 0.2 |
| **I** | `MC_ROLLRATE_I` = 0.2 | `MC_PITCHRATE_I` = 0.2 | `MC_YAWRATE_I` = 0.1 |
| **D** | `MC_ROLLRATE_D` = 0.003 | `MC_PITCHRATE_D` = 0.003 | `MC_YAWRATE_D` = 0.0 |
| **FF** | `MC_ROLLRATE_FF` = 0.0 | `MC_PITCHRATE_FF` = 0.0 | `MC_YAWRATE_FF` = 0.0 |
| **K (master)** | `MC_ROLLRATE_K` = 1.0 | `MC_PITCHRATE_K` = 1.0 | `MC_YAWRATE_K` = 1.0 |
| Integrator clip | `MC_RR_INT_LIM` = 0.30 | `MC_PR_INT_LIM` = 0.30 | `MC_YR_INT_LIM` = 0.30 |
| Output field | `vehicle_torque_setpoint.xyz[0]` ∈ [−1,1] | `.xyz[1]` | `.xyz[2]` |

### 3.4 Where the feedback enters

- The inner loop is triggered by `vehicle_angular_velocity` updates via a callback work-item (`MulticopterRateControl.hpp:106`). Each cycle reads `rates = angular_velocity.xyz` and `angular_accel = angular_velocity.xyz_derivative` (lines 160-161).
- The setpoint is sourced from `vehicle_rates_setpoint` published by the outer loop (line 208-215), with `NaN` per-axis defaulting to `rates(i)` (zero-error per-axis no-op).
- The PID call is at line 248: `_rate_control.update(rates, _rates_setpoint, angular_accel, dt, _maybe_landed || _landed)`.
- Saturation flags from `control_allocator_status.unallocated_torque` are written (lines 226-244) but the anti-windup gate inside `rate_control.cpp` is **commented out** (lines 92-99). Saturation flags currently have no effect on the integrator.

