## 4. Feedback signal sources

Both loops close around the IMU. Here's where the feedback signals come from:

| Signal | Source module | uORB topic / field | Rate | Filters applied |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| **q** — measured attitude (quaternion) | EKF2 | `vehicle_attitude.q` | ~100 Hz | EKF state |
| **ω** — measured body rates | sensors / VehicleAngularVelocity | `vehicle_angular_velocity.xyz` | 250–1000 Hz | calibration + LPF + dynamic notch |
| **α** — angular acceleration | sensors / VehicleAngularVelocity | `vehicle_angular_velocity.xyz_derivative` | same | derivative of filtered ω |

`vehicle_angular_velocity` is produced by `src/modules/sensors/vehicle_angular_velocity/VehicleAngularVelocity.cpp` from raw `sensor_gyro`. The filter stack is governed by `IMU_GYRO_*` parameters.

